{
  "doc_id": "31533",
  "text": "Zuber et al. reported a patient who presented with PE several times after a ligament reconstruction surgery. At first, the patient was only treated with anticoagulation. Echocardiography, which showed RV myxoma, was not performed until the patient presented for the third time [CITATION_1] . The case reported by Boulafendis et al. also shows that echocardiogram was performed during a second presentation after only giving anticoagulation therapy during the first one [CITATION_2] . González et al. reported the death of a 12-year-old boy after failing to diagnose the myxoma early [CITATION_3] . These cases show that the diagnosis of myxomas can be easily missed in case of not suspecting them.",
